            "heading": "Sal Syed",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_YkJbgL": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sal received his MBA from Yale where he was a Fellow at the Yale Entrepreneurial Institute. He has been a featured speaker at Yale University on Entrepreneurship and Leadership topics and belongs to the Young Presidents’ Organization (YPO).</p><p>In 2019, Sal was recognized as the top innovator in golf by the industry-leading publication Golf Inc. Magazine and was the opening keynote speaker at the annual Golf Inc. Summit.</p><p>Prior to Arccos, Sal worked at software startups for more than 10 years as a software engineer, engineering manager, product manager, and data architect.</p><p>Sal is a scratch golfer, a club champion and has notched six holes-in-one (five of which he credits to the power of Arccos). Sal is passionate about course architecture and is a Golf Digest panelist. At Ohio Wesleyan, he was captain of both the Men’s Varsity Tennis Team and the Cricket Team.</p>",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_font": "body",
            "secondary_color": false,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
